<title>Vowels and consonants</title>
<category>ling</category>
<via />
<body>
<p>Last week's New Yorker magazine had a good story on Matthew Carter, a renowned type designer.
They got all the details right, but one factoid they mentioned stood out like a sore thumb.
They said, "Dickens preferred vowels, Thackeray used more consonants".
How could that be?  They were both writing in English in the same time period. How much
personal preference for one letter over another could you express?
</p>

<p>So I did an experiment.  I downloaded plain text versions of
<a href='http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/766'>David Copperfield</a>
and
<a href='http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/599'>Vanity Fair</a>
from
<a href='http://www.gutenberg.org/'>Project Gutenberg</a>.
A quick histogram of the letters in each reveals this distribution of frequency of use (for letters more than 1%):
</p>

<p><table align='center'>
<tr><td colspan='2'>Dickens</td>    <td colspan='2'>Thackeray</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;e&#160;</td><td align='right'>12.08&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;e&#160;</td><td align='right'>12.39&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;t&#160;</td><td align='right'>8.85&#160;</td>         <td>&#160;t&#160;</td><td align='right'>8.43&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;a&#160;</td><td align='right'>8.17&#160;</td>         <td>&#160;a&#160;</td><td align='right'>8.31&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;o&#160;</td><td align='right'>7.74&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;o&#160;</td><td align='right'>7.58&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;i&#160;</td><td align='right'>7.24&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;n&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.78&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;n&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.84&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;h&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.57&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;h&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.06&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;s&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.46&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;s&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.05&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;i&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.41&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;r&#160;</td><td align='right'>5.75&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;r&#160;</td><td align='right'>6.19&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;d&#160;</td><td align='right'>4.70&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;d&#160;</td><td align='right'>4.71&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;l&#160;</td><td align='right'>3.79&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;l&#160;</td><td align='right'>3.97&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;m&#160;</td><td align='right'>3.15&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;u&#160;</td><td align='right'>2.70&#160;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;u&#160;</td><td align='right'>2.83&#160;</td>        <td>&#160;m&#160;</td><td align='right'>2.66&#160;</td></tr>
